        "description": {
            "name": "description",
            "type": "java.lang.String",
            "value": "If PHP was compiled with '--disable-dom', then various classes relied upon by the Zend_Gdata module will not exist and things will break. Right now, this manifests as a \"Class 'DOMDocument' not found\" error.\n\nRather than let this happen, a check should be made to see if the DOM extension is loaded, and if it isn't print a descriptive error message to help users understand the problem."
        },
